The paper focuses on improving the energy efficiency of Multi-Path TCP (MPTCP) for mobile devices, which involves network interfaces and power consumption. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the security implications of MPTCP, which suggests a possible fit for cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The development of an energy model and the evaluation of the proposed solution involve mathematical analysis and optimization, which could fall under cs.MA (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of MPTCP on network performance, which could relate to cs.IT (Information Theory).
